1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,336
<i>My name is Homer Sebastian.</i>

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:05,630
<i>I was in a relationship</i>
<i>with your mother in the past.</i>

3
00:00:05,714 --> 00:00:09,092
<i>If you're wondering who your dad is,</i>

4
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:14,139
<i>I'm also wondering, Olsen,</i>
<i>if you're my son.</i>

5
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:16,182
<i>Olsen is not your son!</i>

6
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:20,103
<i>If you're telling the truth</i>
<i>that Olsen isn't my son,</i>

7
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:23,690
<i>then I can just take my anger out on him.</i>

8
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:25,692
- [GRUNTS]
- [LUCAS] <i>Take that!</i>

9
00:00:25,775 --> 00:00:27,110
<i>Guys, I've got a plan.</i>

10
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:30,488
<i>This is about transmitters and receivers.</i>

11
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,282
<i>These are receivers.</i>

12
00:00:32,365 --> 00:00:37,328
<i>So if we find the transmitter,</i>
<i>we can deactivate the bombs.</i>

13
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:42,792
[CONRAD] <i>Boss, this looks good.</i>

14
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,177
[DADO COUGHS]

15
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:53,970
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [GRUNTS]

16
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:57,682
[LIAM] <i>Get his earpiece.</i>
<i>This way, we can hear their plans.</i>

17
00:00:57,766 --> 00:00:58,892
<i>Tie them up.</i>

18
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:01,352
<i>These guys will stay knocked out</i>
<i>till later, right, Doc?</i>

19
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:04,606
<i>They'll definitely look for these two.</i>

20
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:08,109
<i>We need to find an exit</i>
<i>so I can at least get you out.</i>

21
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:09,611
[JOY] <i>How do we get out?</i>

22
00:01:09,694 --> 00:01:12,072
<i>Every entrance and exit</i>
<i>has a bomb attached.</i>

23
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:13,490
[BOTH GRUNTING]

24
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:16,659
[LUCAS]<i> Brother!</i>

25
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:18,328
<i>Go ahead!</i>

26
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:19,662
- [OLSEN] <i>Ma, don't.</i>
- <i>Stop it!</i>

27
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:21,289
- [OLSEN]<i> Stop!</i>
- [WENDY]<i> That's enough!</i>

28
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:23,875
- <i>It's over.</i>
- [HOMER] <i>Oh, is that so?!</i>

29
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:26,503
- [WENDY] <i>Stop it!</i>
- [OLSEN] <i>You lost!</i>

30
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:28,838
[YELLS]

31
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,089
[GUN CLICKS]

32
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:33,676
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:37,680
[SINGING]
<i>♪ Happy birthday ♪</i>

34
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:39,682
[EERIE MUSIC STING]

35
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:44,020
- [HOMER LAUGHS MANIACALLY]
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:01:44,103 --> 00:01:45,688
[WENDY SOBS]

37
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:49,859
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

38
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:51,194
Cool, right?

39
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:57,867
- [LAUGHING MANIACALLY]
- [DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

40
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:06,543
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

41
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:12,590
- [DEVICE BEEPING]
- [LOW, TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

42
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:20,265
I know what kind of bombs they planted.

43
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:22,225
Military-type IED.

44
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,519
[DEVICE BEEPING]

45
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:25,436
[OFFICER] Sir.

46
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:28,106
You can go up now.

47
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:32,527
[DEVICE BEEPING]

48
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:52,338
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:01,681
[SOBBING]

50
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:02,765
Liam.

51
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,435
What should we do now?

52
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:12,442
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

53
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:23,661
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

54
00:03:31,628 --> 00:03:38,635
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:10,500
[DEVICE BEEPING]

56
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:11,834
[LIAM] Lieutenant!

57
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:14,462
Lieutenant, the bomb here is rigged.

58
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:16,172
We can't move it. It might explode.

59
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:17,507
Do you know how to disarm bombs?

60
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,884
I'll teach you how to disarm a bomb.

61
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,594
- [DEVICE BEEPING]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,930
[AREZA] Be careful with
the wires attached to the bomb.

63
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:27,433
If the firing mechanism gets triggered,
the bomb will explode.

64
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:30,353
You have to control your every move.

65
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:32,063
Listen to everything I say.

66
00:04:32,146 --> 00:04:33,731
Force yourself to stay calm.

67
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:36,359
[HAPPY] Sir Liam,

68
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,194
don't be nervous.

69
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:39,904
You can do it, Sir Liam. You've got this!

70
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:41,656
Are you ready, Liam?

71
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:46,286
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

72
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:47,370
Go over there.

73
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:49,455
- But, sir…
- I said go over there!

74
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:53,668
- Sir…
- Don't move.

75
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:54,669
Be careful.

76
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:58,673
I'm ready.

77
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:05,221
Find the latch

78
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:07,515
at the side of the doorframe.

79
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,310
The latch is here.

80
00:05:10,935 --> 00:05:12,353
- [AREZA] Liam…
- Should I open it?

81
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:14,063
Go ahead and open it.

82
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:15,940
Be careful, Liam.

83
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:19,944
[DEVICE BEEPING]

84
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:23,614
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:25,158
[AREZA] That's it.

86
00:05:25,241 --> 00:05:26,242
Okay, good.

87
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:30,079
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

88
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:32,373
Liam, what do you see?

89
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,752
[LIAM] There's a small control board

90
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:38,212
and a terminal block
numbered one to three.

91
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,756
They share a common ground.

92
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,424
I don't see a wireless receiver.

93
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,551
It might be timer-based
or contact-triggered.

94
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:46,763
[DEVICE BEEPING]

95
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:54,145
[AREZA] It only passes through
terminal number three.

96
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:58,316
The rest are decoy or secondary lines.

97
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:00,276
Don't touch lines one and two.

98
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,403
They're not part of the active circuit.

99
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:04,614
Go, Liam.

100
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:11,412
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [DEVICE BEEPING]

101
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,136
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

102
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:41,609
<i>We start now, Liam.</i>

103
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:48,366
[MAN]<i> This is the tricky part</i>
<i>of cleaning a puffer fish.</i>

104
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:51,577
<i>You need to find the toxic section.</i>

105
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:55,123
<i>It is usually encased in a small sac.</i>

106
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,751
<i>Don't cut it or squeeze it.</i>

107
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:03,756
<i>Lift it up slowly using steady pressure</i>

108
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:06,467
<i>to separate it without tearing it.</i>

109
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:09,137
<i>One wrong move, and the toxin will spill.</i>

110
00:07:09,971 --> 00:07:13,474
<i>The poison will spread through the fish,</i>
<i>and it will no longer be edible.</i>

111
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:18,312
<i>You need to keep your hands steady.</i>
<i>Keep calm.</i>

112
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:19,689
<i>No sudden movements.</i>

113
00:07:19,772 --> 00:07:21,023
[LIAM GRUNTS]

114
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:24,652
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

115
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:30,783
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BOMB BEEPING]

116
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:33,286
[SIGHS IN RELIEF] Good job, Liam.

117
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:34,620
The bomb has been disarmed.

118
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:36,456
Yes! [PANTS]

119
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,166
[SIGHS]

120
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,918
Wait.

121
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:42,628
Are you sure?

122
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:44,255
I'm sure.

123
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:49,969
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

124
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:51,721
Okay.

125
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:54,474
- Let's go!
- Come on!

126
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:56,559
- Come on!
- [SCREAMING]

127
00:07:56,642 --> 00:07:57,685
Come on out!

128
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:03,065
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:06,986
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

130
00:08:07,069 --> 00:08:08,488
[PHONE RINGING]

131
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,865
Lucas, pick up. They're here.

132
00:08:11,824 --> 00:08:12,658
[AREZA] Yes?

133
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:16,746
[LINE DISCONNECTING]

134
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:22,293
Lucas!

135
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:27,632
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,432
They might need help. Let's go.

137
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:41,771
[HAPPY SNIFFLES]

138
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:46,150
I thought I wouldn't be able to
step outside this hospital, sir.

139
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:48,277
Let's get out of here.

140
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:51,072
[HAPPY CRIES]

141
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:54,450
Emil Padua's daughter is in the ward.

142
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:57,245
Most of them are on the rooftop.

143
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:59,997
Okay. We'll handle them.
Good job, Liam.

144
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:04,335
You should go with them.

145
00:09:09,131 --> 00:09:11,008
Doc Ivan, are you okay?

146
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:13,177
- [MILA] Ma'am…
- Yes, thank you.

147
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:15,763
But I need you to check up on Luna.

148
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:18,391
She just had an operation.
She has a bullet wound.

149
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:23,354
Doc, I already told you earlier
that I'm okay.

150
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:24,438
[IVAN SIGHS]

151
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:26,107
You're so stubborn.

152
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:29,402
You need to rest
so you can recover quickly.

153
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:33,614
Lieutenant, before I forget,

154
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:35,157
here's the rifle.

155
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:38,077
Men.

156
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,789
And the hostage-takers were
using this to communicate.

157
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:45,501
[LUNA] Liam, surrender yours too.

158
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:54,844
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:57,638
You're not coming with us, are you?

160
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:00,891
You already know why.

161
00:10:01,892 --> 00:10:05,313
Sir, it's too dangerous.

162
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,149
Don't go back inside.

163
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:09,609
I have to do this.

164
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:11,694
There are still
a lot of them left in there.

165
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:15,239
Dude.

166
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:17,450
Dude.

167
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:20,328
[LIAM] Go.

168
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:24,624
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:26,292
- Luna, let's go.
- Go.

170
00:10:30,546 --> 00:10:32,632
- [AREZA] Requesting backup.
- [HAPPY] Sir, be careful.

171
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:34,759
[AREZA] We now have
safe entry points to St. John's.

172
00:10:35,384 --> 00:10:36,510
We can enter the building now.

173
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:38,888
Lieutenant. Wait a second.

174
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:48,314
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

175
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:55,446
I really don't understand
why you had to meddle.

176
00:10:57,907 --> 00:10:59,283
Didn't you see?

177
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,412
They were going to kill Olsen.

178
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:06,040
Olsen is not your son.

179
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,752
He's probably the son of that monster.

180
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:16,634
Olsen is like a son to me.

181
00:11:16,717 --> 00:11:18,511
You know that.

182
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:21,597
I won't just abandon him.

183
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:25,476
Did you really do that for Olsen,

184
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:28,270
or was it for Wendy?

185
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,272
Greta, please.

186
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:32,608
Come on, no.

187
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:35,903
Do you still love Wendy?

188
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,991
It doesn't matter now.

189
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:43,369
It matters, Magnus.

190
00:11:44,745 --> 00:11:47,331
You know what matters, hmm?

191
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:50,751
It's the promise we made to each other.

192
00:11:52,461 --> 00:11:55,297
After what happened with Ayen.

193
00:11:57,174 --> 00:12:01,637
We will stick together as a family
no matter what.

194
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:05,266
That is what matters.

195
00:12:05,349 --> 00:12:09,061
You should be thinking about that
and our son.

196
00:12:10,187 --> 00:12:12,022
I trust Liam.

197
00:12:12,731 --> 00:12:15,818
But you? You just lost my trust again.

198
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:20,906
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:31,083
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:32,835
[TAPS]

201
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:39,925
[SIREN WAILING]

202
00:12:45,681 --> 00:12:49,101
We sedated some of the hostage takers.

203
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:51,270
If the other hostage takers
find out about it,

204
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:56,025
I'm sure they're going to hurt my parents
and the other hostages inside.

205
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:58,944
That's why we're going to do
a surprise attack.

206
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:01,530
They said

207
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:03,949
it's better if we take this way.

208
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:06,494
Sir.

209
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:09,872
Extracting the hostages won't be easy.

210
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:12,082
There are bombs attached to them.

211
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:15,169
They will automatically explode
if they run away.

212
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,839
They used a transmitter
and receiver module.

213
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:22,801
After we secure the hostages,

214
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,970
that's when we're going
to remove the bombs.

215
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:26,305
We need to move fast.

216
00:13:27,264 --> 00:13:29,308
Before the sedated guys
regain consciousness.

217
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:33,729
- [AREZA] Which area are they in?
- [LIAM] That'll take too long.

218
00:13:33,812 --> 00:13:36,106
- I'll just show you where it is.
- Liam!

219
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:48,494
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

220
00:13:55,751 --> 00:14:02,132
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

221
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:24,780
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

222
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:29,952
[HOMER GRUNTS]

223
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:39,295
[HOMER EXHALES DEEPLY]

224
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:47,720
Is it true, Homer?

225
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:51,015
There's a possibility that
the security guy is your son?

226
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:57,730
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:14:58,647 --> 00:15:00,649
That Wendy is a pro, I guess.

228
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:04,820
Did you know that she
and Magnus Roja had an affair?

229
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:07,615
What?

230
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:24,006
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:25,215
Psst.

232
00:15:32,556 --> 00:15:33,766
What did you do?

233
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:35,809
I broke the transmitter.

234
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:39,688
The bombs won't explode
even if we're far away.

235
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:42,316
Macky.

236
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,277
[RITA] Are you sure?

237
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:48,155
What if it suddenly explodes?

238
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:50,199
Macky's right.

239
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:54,411
They use the transmitter
to trigger the bomb,

240
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,705
using distance as a trigger.

241
00:15:57,414 --> 00:15:59,750
Now that the transmitter is broken,

242
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,377
the bombs are useless.

243
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:04,088
Good job.

244
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,839
So, what are we going to do now?

245
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:09,301
If we attack them together,

246
00:16:10,886 --> 00:16:12,680
we might be able to stand a chance.

247
00:16:12,763 --> 00:16:14,056
No, no.

248
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:16,433
That's not a good plan.

249
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:18,644
I think it's not a great idea.

250
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:21,063
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:22,773
[FIN] Are you serious?

252
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:24,942
It's too dangerous.

253
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:26,443
We're defenseless.

254
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:27,820
They're armed.

255
00:16:27,903 --> 00:16:33,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:16:39,915 --> 00:16:44,336
Magnus might be the reason
Wendy left the resort.

257
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:47,214
And she went with you.

258
00:16:48,632 --> 00:16:50,259
You're just her rebound.

259
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:52,720
[CHUCKLES]

260
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:58,726
But it's not impossible
that the security guy is your son.

261
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,894
[LUCAS] Admit it.

262
00:17:01,478 --> 00:17:02,813
He takes after you.

263
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:04,064
He's tough.

264
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:07,026
And if this had been real…

265
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:09,194
[GUN CLICKS]

266
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:11,155
…you would've shot his brains out earlier.

267
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:15,284
[CHUCKLING]

268
00:17:20,497 --> 00:17:23,333
But I'm still not sure
about him being my son.

269
00:17:24,168 --> 00:17:26,045
His mother denied it, remember?

270
00:17:26,795 --> 00:17:28,422
But if there's a chance that it's true,

271
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,549
wouldn't you prefer that?

272
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:32,384
Someone can finally replace Junior.

273
00:17:34,261 --> 00:17:35,679
[LUCAS GRUNTS]

274
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:38,766
My son is irreplaceable.

275
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:40,642
Do you understand?!

276
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:42,770
- Hmm?!
- [LUCAS GRUNTS]

277
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:47,399
[GROANING]

278
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:54,323
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

279
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:58,202
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

280
00:17:58,285 --> 00:17:59,912
- [GRUNTS]
- Are you okay?

281
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:04,208
Lucas.

282
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:07,961
What happened to him and his son?

283
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:13,592
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:15,260
Homer was driving at that time.

285
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:16,804
He was drunk.

286
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:20,224
His son was in the car with him.

287
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:24,269
They got into an accident.

288
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:30,901
Homer is still blaming himself
for Junior's death even now.

289
00:18:30,984 --> 00:18:37,241
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

290
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,042
[RIFLE THUDS]

291
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:56,802
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,470
Is he really my father?

293
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,267
Tell me the truth, Ma.

294
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:05,477
Please.

295
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,528
Yes.

296
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:18,615
But you don't need him anymore.

297
00:19:24,454 --> 00:19:27,082
How can you say I don't need him?

298
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:36,300
Ma, from childhood, I'd accepted…

299
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,680
that I would never meet my dad.

300
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:44,266
Because he's dead.

301
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:47,269
All my life,
I thought he was already gone.

302
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:50,189
But you know, when I was a kid…

303
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:57,237
I'd always get jealous whenever
I saw kids with their fathers.

304
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:00,449
Now,

305
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,534
I find out…

306
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,830
that he's still alive.

307
00:20:06,914 --> 00:20:11,877
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

308
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:14,213
I grew up well, yes.

309
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,964
I had Grandpa.

310
00:20:17,341 --> 00:20:18,717
I even had Sir Magnus.

311
00:20:20,677 --> 00:20:25,224
But I hope you understand
where I'm coming from.

312
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:28,018
It's still different…

313
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,773
to get to know who my real father is.

314
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:40,822
You already saw what kind of person he is.

315
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:46,036
Do you still want to recognize him
as your father?

316
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:52,125
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:21:01,718 --> 00:21:05,597
<i>I only found out now who my</i>
<i>real father is, and it's you.</i>

318
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:08,183
<i>- What do you want to happen?</i>
<i>- Let Mama go.</i>

319
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,851
[GRETA] <i>Why aren't you</i>
<i>stopping your son?</i>

320
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:11,645
<i>He's going to get all of us in trouble.</i>

321
00:21:11,728 --> 00:21:12,854
[MACKY] <i>I've had enough!</i>

322
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:15,107
<i>If you leave, you're going to explode!</i>
<i>You're going to die!</i>

323
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:16,608
[MACKY] <i>Let me go!</i>

324
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:19,319
[FIN] <i>Why? Just because you're</i>
<i>the senator's son?!</i>

325
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:21,029
<i>- You really won't stop?!</i>
- [GUNSHOT]

326
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,781
- [LIAM]<i> Let's go.</i>
- [AREZA]<i> Let's move!</i>

327
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:24,700
[LIAM] <i>I'm going to talk to Emil Padua.</i>

328
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:26,743
<i>I can't let you attack them like this.</i>

329
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:29,496
<i>If something happens to them,</i>
<i>it'll be my fault!</i>

330
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:31,248
<i>You are involved in what's happening.</i>

331
00:21:31,331 --> 00:21:34,751
<i>If you want to know everything,</i>
<i>I'll tell you, sir.</i>

332
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:43,093
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
